comments.body:
@LilithHafner Thanks a lot for the fast response. The thing is that my app SpmImageTycoon relies very heavily on Blink. My app is geared towards end users (it is a GUI app) and not towards coders. And I want them to be able to just install it and start it very easily. And I have not found a way to specify a specific branch or commit in the project compats.

The current release of Blink hangs with Julia 1.10 during precompilation, so my app is not working (the problems are fixed on github, just that the version is not released yet). I had a similar problem when when Julia 1.9 was released, so I thought the best way to keep my app working is to have a designated prerelease package. 

And this is in no way meant as criticism of the maintainers - Blink.jl is a great package, I really really like it and I am very grateful to the creators and maintainers, who are doing a great job! Just that it makes me nervous that my app currently can't be installed.
